h3cIpx.name: h3cIpx
h3cIpx.contactinfo: Mib Team Platform Team Huawei 3Com Technologies Co.,Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085
h3cIpx.description: This mib defines management information used on products which support ipx protocol. It includes 4 parts: 1.ipx interface configuration group - This group contains configurable management information and statistic information on each interface. 2.rip group - Rip means route information protocol. This group contains configurable management information and route status and route statistic information. 3.sap group - Sap means service access group. This group contains all service information. 4.ipx statistics group - This group includes ipx statistic information on all interfaces.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

h3cIpxStatus.name: h3cIpxStatus
h3cIpxStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable ipx globally.

h3cIpxIfConfigTable.name: h3cIpxIfConfigTable
h3cIpxIfConfigTable.description: Table of configurable management information on each interface.

h3cIpxIfConfigEntry.name: h3cIpxIfConfigEntry
h3cIpxIfConfigEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing management information about a single interface.

h3cIpxIfIndex.name: h3cIpxIfIndex
h3cIpxIfIndex.description: This variable uniquely identifies the interface to which the configurations are applied.

h3cIpxIfNetId.name: h3cIpxIfNetId
h3cIpxIfNetId.description: The network number of the IPX address of this interface.

h3cIpxIfNodeId.name: h3cIpxIfNodeId
h3cIpxIfNodeId.description: The node number of the IPX address of this interface.

h3cIpxIfSplitHorizon.name: h3cIpxIfSplitHorizon
h3cIpxIfSplitHorizon.description: This node is used to set the split horizon status. Its default value is 'enabled'. In this case, the interface which receives a message can't send this message from the same interface. This function can avoid route loop. But it is unused for point to point link. If it is set to 'disabled', split horizon is disable.

h3cIPxIfTick.name: h3cIPxIfTick
h3cIPxIfTick.description: This object is used to set this interface's delay time. It is counted by ticks which is 1/18 second. By default, the ethernet interface's delay time is 1 tick, asynchronous serial interface's delay time is 30 ticks, WAN interface's delay time is 6 ticks.

h3cIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly.name: h3cIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly
h3cIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly.description: When this variable is set to 'enabled', updating change is on. And sap and rip will send updating packets periodically to avoid broadcast storm. Whereas updating change is off.

h3cIpxIfRipMtu.name: h3cIpxIfRipMtu
h3cIpxIfRipMtu.description: This variable is used to define the max length of RIP updating packets.

h3cIpxIfEncapsuleType.name: h3cIpxIfEncapsuleType
h3cIpxIfEncapsuleType.description: This node is used to define the encapsulating form of IPX packets. 'dot2' indicates the form is 802.2, while 'dot3' means 802.3. And 'snap' indicates the form is ethernet-snap. It takes effect only on ethernet interface, and the default value is 'dot3', while 'unkown' for other types of port.

h3cIpxIfNetbiosPropagation.name: h3cIpxIfNetbiosPropagation
h3cIpxIfNetbiosPropagation.description: This node is used to configure whether the current interface can forward broadcasting packets which IPX type is 20 used for NetBIOS.

h3cIpxIfSapStatus.name: h3cIpxIfSapStatus
h3cIpxIfSapStatus.description: The status of sap on the current interface. It is enabled when ipx is enabled on this interface.

h3cIpxIfSapMtu.name: h3cIpxIfSapMtu
h3cIpxIfSapMtu.description: This variable is used to define the max length of SAP refreshing packets.

h3cIpxIfGnsReply.name: h3cIpxIfGnsReply
h3cIpxIfGnsReply.description: This object is used to enable or disable the current interface to response the IPX GNS request.

h3cIpxIfRowStatus.name: h3cIpxIfRowStatus
h3cIpxIfRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

h3cIpxRouteMultiplier.name: h3cIpxRouteMultiplier
h3cIpxRouteMultiplier.description: This node is used to calculate Rip aging time of route information. The absolute aging time = (h3cIpxRouteMultiplier * h3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer).

h3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer.name: h3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer
h3cIpxRouteUpdateTimer.description: This node is used to set rip updating time which is based on seconds

h3cIpxRouteImpRouteStatic.name: h3cIpxRouteImpRouteStatic
h3cIpxRouteImpRouteStatic.description: This object determines whether static route can be imported.

h3cIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths.name: h3cIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths
h3cIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths.description: This object defines the max equivalent paths to the same destination. If the newly defined value is smaller than the current value, the routes out of the new value will be set inactive.

h3cIpxRouteMaxResPaths.name: h3cIpxRouteMaxResPaths
h3cIpxRouteMaxResPaths.description: This object defines the max dynamic routes to the same destination. If the newly defined value is smaller than the current value, the routes will not be deleted until they age out or are deleted manually.

h3cIpxRouteTable.name: h3cIpxRouteTable
h3cIpxRouteTable.description: This table contains all dynamic and direct ipx route information of this system. The information of this table is read only.

h3cIpxRouteEntry.name: h3cIpxRouteEntry
h3cIpxRouteEntry.description: Each entry includes a dynamic or direct route.

h3cIpxRouteIndex.name: h3cIpxRouteIndex
h3cIpxRouteIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a route.

h3cIpxRouteDestNetId.name: h3cIpxRouteDestNetId
h3cIpxRouteDestNetId.description: The destination network number of this route information, and its value ranges from 1 to 0xfffffffe.

h3cIpxRouteNextHop.name: h3cIpxRouteNextHop
h3cIpxRouteNextHop.description: The next hop of this route.

h3cIpxRoutePro.name: h3cIpxRoutePro
h3cIpxRoutePro.description: The protocol type of this route information.

h3cIpxRoutePre.name: h3cIpxRoutePre
h3cIpxRoutePre.description: The preference of this route information. The direct route's preference is 0, and it can't be modified. Dynamic route's default preference is 100.

h3cIpxRouteTicks.name: h3cIpxRouteTicks
h3cIpxRouteTicks.description: The time, in ticks, that the packet takes to reach the destination.

h3cIpxRouteHops.name: h3cIpxRouteHops
h3cIpxRouteHops.description: The object indicates the number of hops that the packet must be passed through to reach the destination.

h3cIpxRouteTime.name: h3cIpxRouteTime
h3cIpxRouteTime.description: The aging time of this route information. The aging time of static and interface route information is 0.

h3cIpxRouteOutInterface.name: h3cIpxRouteOutInterface
h3cIpxRouteOutInterface.description: The out interface of this route information.

h3cIpxStaticRouteTable.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteTable
h3cIpxStaticRouteTable.description: This table contains all static ipx route information of this system.

h3cIpxStaticRouteEntry.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteEntry
h3cIpxStaticRouteEntry.description: Each entry includes one static route information.

h3cIpxStaticRouteDestNetId.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteDestNetId
h3cIpxStaticRouteDestNetId.description: The index of Static Route Table. This object and h3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop uniquely identify a static route. The destination network number of this static route information,and its value ranges from 1 to 0xfffffffe. Note that the broadcast network number is 0xffffffff and is not allowed in IPX. The network number of 0xfffffffe would be considered to be the network number of default route.

h3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop
h3cIpxStaticRouteNextHop.description: The sub-index of Static Route Table. The next hop of this static route information.

h3cIpxStaticRoutePre.name: h3cIpxStaticRoutePre
h3cIpxStaticRoutePre.description: The preference of this route information. Static route's preference is 60, and it can be configured.

h3cIpxStaticRouteOutIf.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteOutIf
h3cIpxStaticRouteOutIf.description: The out interface of this route. This interface can be serial or pos interface.

h3cIpxStaticRouteTicks.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteTicks
h3cIpxStaticRouteTicks.description: The time, in ticks that the packet takes to reach the destination with the static route.

h3cIpxStaticRouteHops.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteHops
h3cIpxStaticRouteHops.description: This object indicates how many hops are needed to arrive at the destination network.

h3cIpxStaticRouteStatus.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteStatus
h3cIpxStaticRouteStatus.description: The status of this static route.

h3cIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.name: h3cIpxStaticRouteRowStatus
h3cIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

h3cIpxRouteStatTable.name: h3cIpxRouteStatTable
h3cIpxRouteStatTable.description: A table includes all statistic route information.

h3cIpxRouteStatEntry.name: h3cIpxRouteStatEntry
h3cIpxRouteStatEntry.description: An entry records a statistic information of route.

h3cIpxRouteStatPro.name: h3cIpxRouteStatPro
h3cIpxRouteStatPro.description: The protocol type of the route information. The value of 'total' is the total amount of all kinds of IPX routes.

h3cIpxRouteStatRoutes.name: h3cIpxRouteStatRoutes
h3cIpxRouteStatRoutes.description: The route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

h3cIpxRouteStatActives.name: h3cIpxRouteStatActives
h3cIpxRouteStatActives.description: The active route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

h3cIpxRouteStatAddeds.name: h3cIpxRouteStatAddeds
h3cIpxRouteStatAddeds.description: The added route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

h3cIpxRouteStatDeleteds.name: h3cIpxRouteStatDeleteds
h3cIpxRouteStatDeleteds.description: The deleted but not freed route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

h3cIpxRouteStatFreeds.name: h3cIpxRouteStatFreeds
h3cIpxRouteStatFreeds.description: The freed route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

h3cIpxSapMultiplier.name: h3cIpxSapMultiplier
h3cIpxSapMultiplier.description: This node is used to calculate aging time of service information. The absolute aging time = (h3cIpxSapMultiplier * h3cIpxSapUpdateTimer).

h3cIpxSapUpdateTimer.name: h3cIpxSapUpdateTimer
h3cIpxSapUpdateTimer.description: This node is used to set service packet updating time which is based on seconds.

h3cIpxSapGnsLoadBalance.name: h3cIpxSapGnsLoadBalance
h3cIpxSapGnsLoadBalance.description: This object is used to set whether the system will reply to the GNS request with the Round-Robin way. By default, the system will response to the GNS request with the servers known to the device in turn, preventing from the nearest server's over loading. With value of disabled, in this way, the system will response to the request with the nearest server(who has smallest hop in system's service information table).

h3cIpxSapMaxResServers.name: h3cIpxSapMaxResServers
h3cIpxSapMaxResServers.description: This object is used to configure maximum number of servers of a type. If the newly defined value is smaller than the previous value, the information out of the value will not be deleted. If the queue reaches to the maximum number, no new information can be added.

h3cIpxServiceTable.name: h3cIpxServiceTable
h3cIpxServiceTable.description: This table inlcudes all dynamic service information. The dynamic service information can be read only.

h3cIpxServiceIndex.name: h3cIpxServiceIndex
h3cIpxServiceIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a service information.

h3cIpxServiceNetId.name: h3cIpxServiceNetId
h3cIpxServiceNetId.description: The IPX network number portion of the IPX address of the service.

h3cIpxServiceNodeId.name: h3cIpxServiceNodeId
h3cIpxServiceNodeId.description: The IPX node number portion of the IPX address of the service.

h3cIpxServiceSocketNo.name: h3cIpxServiceSocketNo
h3cIpxServiceSocketNo.description: The socket portion of the IPX address of the service

h3cIpxServicePreference.name: h3cIpxServicePreference
h3cIpxServicePreference.description: The service preference of the service

h3cIpxServiceHops.name: h3cIpxServiceHops
h3cIpxServiceHops.description: The hops from the device to the server.

h3cIpxServiceRecvIf.name: h3cIpxServiceRecvIf
h3cIpxServiceRecvIf.description: Interface from which the service is receieved

h3cIpxStaticServiceTable.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceTable
h3cIpxStaticServiceTable.description: This table inlcudes all static service information. This table supports to creation and deletione of a static service, but not supports to modification

h3cIpxStaticServiceType.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceType
h3cIpxStaticServiceType.description: The index of static service table.

h3cIpxStaticServiceName.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceName
h3cIpxStaticServiceName.description: The sub-index of static service table. The name of the service.

h3cIpxStaticServiceNetId.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceNetId
h3cIpxStaticServiceNetId.description: The sub-index of static service table. The IPX network number portion of the IPX address of the service.

h3cIpxStaticServiceNodeId.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceNodeId
h3cIpxStaticServiceNodeId.description: The IPX node number portion of the IPX address of the service.

h3cIpxStatciServiceSocketNo.name: h3cIpxStatciServiceSocketNo
h3cIpxStatciServiceSocketNo.description: The socket portion of the IPX address of the service.

h3cIpxStaticServicePreference.name: h3cIpxStaticServicePreference
h3cIpxStaticServicePreference.description: The service preference of the server.

h3cIpxStaticServiceHops.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceHops
h3cIpxStaticServiceHops.description: The hops from the device to the server.

h3cIpxStaticServiceStatus.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceStatus
h3cIpxStaticServiceStatus.description: The status of the service that you created. The value of this object is determined by system.

h3cIpxStaticServiceRowStatus.name: h3cIpxStaticServiceRowStatus
h3cIpxStaticServiceRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

h3cIpxStatTotalReceives.name: h3cIpxStatTotalReceives
h3cIpxStatTotalReceives.description: The total number of packets received.

h3cIpxStatPitchs.name: h3cIpxStatPitchs
h3cIpxStatPitchs.description: The number of received packets filled by device when forwarding or delivering up to upper protocol.

h3cIpxStatLenErrors.name: h3cIpxStatLenErrors
h3cIpxStatLenErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to length error.

h3cIpxStatFormatErrors.name: h3cIpxStatFormatErrors
h3cIpxStatFormatErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to format error.

h3cIpxStatBadHops.name: h3cIpxStatBadHops
h3cIpxStatBadHops.description: The number of received packets which's value of field Hops is greater than 16.

h3cIpxStatHopsDiscards.name: h3cIpxStatHopsDiscards
h3cIpxStatHopsDiscards.description: The number of received packets of which hops portion is equal to 16.

h3cIpxStatOtherErrors.name: h3cIpxStatOtherErrors
h3cIpxStatOtherErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to other error.

h3cIpxStatLocalDests.name: h3cIpxStatLocalDests
h3cIpxStatLocalDests.description: The number of received packets which destination is the local device. Note that this would include the IPX NetBIOS propagation packets and those broadcast packets just to the network on which local device resides.

h3cIpxStatCantDeals.name: h3cIpxStatCantDeals
h3cIpxStatCantDeals.description: The number of received packets with which can't be dealt. One possible reason for discarding such a packet would be receiving a packet of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

h3cIpxStatForwards.name: h3cIpxStatForwards
h3cIpxStatForwards.description: The number of received packets to be forwarded in the case that the entity was not their final destination.

h3cIpxStatGenerates.name: h3cIpxStatGenerates
h3cIpxStatGenerates.description: The number of sent packets that the device generated itself.

h3cIpxStatNoRoutes.name: h3cIpxStatNoRoutes
h3cIpxStatNoRoutes.description: The number of packets discarded due to no route to the destination was found in routing table.

h3cIpxStatOutDiscards.name: h3cIpxStatOutDiscards
h3cIpxStatOutDiscards.description: The number of packets to be discarded when sending out. Note that this counter would not include the packet(s) discarded due to no route.

h3cIpxStatRipSends.name: h3cIpxStatRipSends
h3cIpxStatRipSends.description: The total number of RIP packets sent.

h3cIpxStatRipReceives.name: h3cIpxStatRipReceives
h3cIpxStatRipReceives.description: The total number of RIP packets received.

h3cIpxStaRipRspReceives.description: The total number of RIP response packets received.

h3cIpxStatRipReqReceives.name: h3cIpxStatRipReqReceives
h3cIpxStatRipReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP request packets received.

h3cIpxStatRipReqDeals.name: h3cIpxStatRipReqDeals
h3cIpxStatRipReqDeals.description: The total number of RIP request packets dealt with.

h3cIpxStatSapSpecReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP specific request packets received.

h3cIpxStatSapGnsReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP GNS request packets received.

h3cIpxStatSapGenRspSends.name: h3cIpxStatSapGenRspSends
h3cIpxStatSapGenRspSends.description: The total number of SAP general response packets sent.

h3cIpxStatSapGnsRspSends.description: The total number of SAP GNS response packets sent.

h3cIpxStatSapInPktErrors.name: h3cIpxStatSapInPktErrors
h3cIpxStatSapInPktErrors.description: The total number of SAP error packets received.

h3cIpxIfStatTable.description: The table of the statistic information on each interface.

h3cIpxIfStatRipReceives.description: The total number of RIP packets received on the interface.

h3cIpxIfStatRipSpecRspSends.description: The total number of RIP specific response packets sent on the interface.

h3cIpxIfStatRipGenReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP general request packets received on the interface.

h3cIpxIfStatRipGenRspSends.description: The total number of RIP general response packets sent on the interface.

h3cIpxIfStatSapReceives.description: The total number of SAP packets received on the interface.
